title: Love Island's Vanessa Sierra reveals Rhyce Power 'put her off dating'
text:
She was sent packing from Love Island Australia on Monday night's episode after spending just three weeks in the villa.

And Vanessa Sierra has now revealed the real reason she decided to sign up for the raunchy dating show.

The 25-year-old model told HuffPost Australia that she put her future in the hands of producers because her last relationship with Rhyce Power had ended badly.

'I didn't trust myself': Vanessa Sierra (right) has revealed she signed up for Love Island after her ex-boyfriend Rhyce Power (left) 'put her off dating' in the real world. Pictured in March

'The level I was burnt by my last relationship put me off dating,' she said.

'I kind of didn't trust myself dating in the normal world and so I actually said this to my best friend, "Well, if I put my dating life in the hands of producers I feel like I'm going to make better choices than if I were in the outside world."'

Vanessa coupled up with model Matt Zukowski at the start of the season, with the pair branding themselves the 'king and queen of the villa'.

Dethroned! Vanessa was eliminated from Love Island on Monday's episode. Pictured with Matt Zukowski (right), whom she coupled up with at the start of the season

But she was eliminated after the duo ended up in the bottom three couples and some of the remaining islanders accused her of playing a game.

Vanessa had her ups and downs with Matt and said after leaving the villa that she has no plans to catch up with him back in Australia.

'I do not believe that Matt was genuine with me,' she said. 'I don't think I'll be waiting for him on the outside.'

Instead, she hopes to reunite with fellow evictee Sam Withers, who was sent home the week before her.

Gone! Vanessa and Maurice Salib (left) were sent packing on Monday's episode and have since returned to Australia

Potential couple? Vanessa hopes to reunite with fellow evictee Sam Withers (pictured), who was sent home the week before her

Vanessa dated Rhyce, the brother of Married At First Sight star Jessika Power, for several months at the start of the year, before ending things in March.

Following their split, she alleged that Rhyce had assaulted her during a fitness holiday in Thailand - which he denies - and later filed an intervention order in Australia.

Under the Victorian intervention order, which is similar to an apprehended violence order (AVO), the heavily-tattooed tradesman is banned from contacting Vanessa.

authors: Jess Bell For Daily Mail Australia
